We are experiencing high demand in SGP1 region for C2 and B2 instance. As a result, stock is limited, and you may encounter error when spawning these instances in SGP1.

Dear customers,

In order to avoid last minute migration, we will temporary stop connectivity to your clusters, one week before shutdown.
No actions required, we will disallow connection during short timeslots and then re-allow connections

Timeline
-	Monday 07/06/2022  14h00 CEST // 10 minutes interruption
-	Friday 10/06/2022 - 14h00 CEST // 30 minutes interruption

As part of the product lifecycle management, We will end the Sales of Enterprise Cloud Databases services January 16th 2022 (no more new services). We will end the Growth of existing Enterprise Cloud Databases services May 16th 2022 (no more new nodes) We will end the Support of all Enterprise Cloud Databases services June 16th 2022 (shutdown of the services). Impacted customers will be notified by email and via control panel about this End-Of-Life process. We will cut-off the services the week before End of Support during punctual 2 hours time slot, to warn impacted customers. Perimeter: All PostgreSQL Enterprise Cloud Databases clusters, worldwide. Related product page: [FR] https://www.ovhcloud.com/fr/enterprise/products/enterprise-cloud-databases/ [EN] https://www.ovhcloud.com/en-ie/enterprise/products/enterprise-cloud-databases/ NOT in the Perimeter: Public Cloud Databases Web Hosting Cloud Databases Workaround: customer will be contacted to migrate to new Public Cloud Databases for PostgreSQL. Migration tutorials and Professional Services will be provided on https://docs.ovh.com/gb/en/enterprise-cloud-databases/ Timeline: 17/01/2022 10h CEST : End of Sales 16/05/2022 10h CEST : End of Growth 10/06/2022 10h-14h CEST : planned downtime 13/06/2022 10h CEST : End of Support, Shutdown of all impacted services 10h CEST We will update this task during the proposed timeline.

Start time : 19/05/2022 08:00 UTC End time : 19/05/2022 14:00 UTC Service impact : You may experience some ping loss (less than 5 seconds) during this upgrade. Service improvement : We will upgrade a core network component (openvswitch) on BHS3 and BHS5 OpenStack region

Start time : 23/05/2022 08:00 UTC End time : 23/05/2022 14:00 UTC Service impact : You may experience some ping loss (less than 5 seconds) during this upgrade. Service improvement : We will upgrade a core network component (openvswitch) on WAW1 and DE1 OpenStack region

Start time : 24/05/2022 08:00 UTC End time : 24/05/2022 14:00 UTC Service impact : You may experience some ping loss (less than 5 seconds) during this upgrade. Service improvement : We will upgrade a core network component (openvswitch) on GRA3, GRA5 and GRA11 OpenStack region

Start time : 25/05/2022 08:00 UTC End time : 25/05/2022 14:00 UTC Service impact : You may experience some ping loss (less than 5 seconds) during this upgrade. Service improvement : We will upgrade a core network component (openvswitch) on GRA1, GRA7 and SBG5 OpenStack region
This maintenance is postponed for the from 31/05/2022 19:00 UTC to 01/06/2022 01:00 UTC.
This maintenance is postponed for the 17/05/2022 from 17:00 UTC to 23:00 UTC.
We will be undergoing scheduled maintenance during this time.
Due to an imponderable we postpone the upgrade operation to Stein for 19/04 from 19h00 UTC to 01h00 UTC

Start time : 15/06/2022 12:00 UTC End time : 15/06/2022 15:00 UTC Service impact : No downtime expected in term of log ingestion, but ES API will not be available for a maximum time of two hours. Service improvement: The indexation backend of Logs Data Platform will be replaced from Elasticsearch to OpenSearch. Kibana instances will be replaced by OpenSearch Dashboards ones. APIv6 calls related to ElasticSearch backend will be automatically redirected to new OpenSearch backend and will remain available until September 2022. The following documentation : https://docs.ovh.com/fr/logs-data-platform/ will be updated few days before the migration.
